getSection

public java.util.List<javax.xml.bind.JAXBElement<? extends SectionType>> getSection()
Specific ovf:Section with additional information for the vApp. Gets the value of the section property.

This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the section property.

For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

    getSection().add(newItem);

Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list JAXBElement<DiskSectionType> JAXBElement<StartupSectionType> JAXBElement<NetworkConnectionSectionType> JAXBElement<NetworkConfigSectionType> JAXBElement<GuestCustomizationSectionType> JAXBElement<ResourceAllocationSectionType> JAXBElement<CustomizationSectionType> JAXBElement<DeploymentOptionSectionType> JAXBElement<EulaSectionType> JAXBElement<ProductSectionType> JAXBElement<NetworkSectionType> JAXBElement<RuntimeInfoSectionType> JAXBElement<SectionType> JAXBElement<VirtualHardwareSectionType> JAXBElement<LeaseSettingsSectionType> JAXBElement<InstallSectionType> JAXBElement<AnnotationSectionType> JAXBElement<OperatingSystemSectionType>
